  "text": "The interactions between periodontal pathogens and the immune response of the organism require knowledge of the pathogenesis of periodontal disease. The activation of dental plaque bacteria involves the development of local and systemic humoral and cellular immunity. The illness is characterized by accumulation of lymphocytes in the periodontal tissues; the inflammatory infiltrate is dominated at the beginning by T lymphocytes while the later chronic phase shows the shift to B lymphocytes and plasma cells [CITATION_1] .",
